Package sailpoint.object

Class Workflow.Return

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      • sailpoint.object.Workflow.Return
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject
    Enclosing class:
    Workflow
    public static class Workflow.Return
extends AbstractXmlObject
    The representation of a return value from a step or approval. For Approval what you are doing is defining the things that will be copied from the WorkItem back into the workflow case. This is an alternative to using the "return" property that allows transformation of the name or value. For Step this is relevant only for subprocess calls, it defines the variables in the subcase to be copied up to the parent case.

      • getEffectiveTo

        public java.lang.String getEffectiveTo()
        Return the name of the destination workflow variable. This will be the same as "to" if set, otherwise is the same as "name". This allows you to return a work item variable under a different name.
